  "texts": [
    "Forward and counterfactual simulatability, that are common in NLP (Xie et al., 2022; Arora et al., 2022), are human-but not application-grounded; Buçinca et al. (2020) show that explanations affect simulatability and human-AI decision-making differently.",
    "Reliance definitions.",
    "It is often asserted that explanations can deter people from rejecting correct predictions, i.e., underreliance.",
    "This expectation stems from assuming that the model is correct for the right reasons, and explanations are anticipated to unveil this.",
    "Explanations could also aid people in rejecting incorrect predictions, thereby countering overreliance."
  ],
